condition.narrative: Should contribute directly to results for children as outlined in the UNDAF, national results and/or UNICEF Strategic Plan and within the scope defined in the CPD, CPAP, OMP or other agreed upon programme documents

title.narrative: Girls and boys without care and victims of abuse, violence and exploitation benefit from social basic services and childprotection
NGOs providing child protection assistance to girls and boys

baseline.value: 1 NGO providing legal assistance to girls and boys without care .

target.value: 2015:5 NGOs providing legal assistance and providing adequate child protection services.

title.narrative: A multi-sectorial national coordination body for child protection exists

baseline.value: Child Trafficking and harmful practices Committees in place.

target.value: 2015:National committees for child protection fully operational

actual.value: 2015:Ongoing. So far no national coordination body. CP Cluster groups operational.

title.narrative: National Child Protection Policy and Action Plan exist Y/N.

baseline.value: No CP Policy nor National Action Plan.

target.value: 2015:Main orientations for the National Child Protection Policy and Action Plan validated amongst stakeholders

title.narrative: girls and boys in contact with the justice system receiving psycho-social legal services

baseline.value: No data on girls and boys receiving psycho-social legal services

target.value: 2015:250 boys and girls receive psycho-social-legal services

title.narrative: % of girls and boys victims of violence, exploitation and abuse (re)integrated in families and/or community

target.value: 2015:50% of returned trafficked children are reintegrated as well as all identified children victims of violence

actual.value: 2015:48 talibes children victims of exploitation were assisted, benefited from psychosocial support and were reintegrated into their communities and families,

title.narrative: courts, social service providers, police stations, and NGOs using sex disaggregated data collected to monitor and improve services and children's situation

baseline.value: No information management system for child protection

target.value: 2015:Sex- disaggregated data recorded and centralized and used by the Institute of Mother and Children

actual.value: 2015:In progress Sex-disaggregated data on violence against children and institutionalized children collected by main CP actors. Major constraints to centralize and use available data persists.

title.narrative: of regions providing protection services to vulnerable girls and boys

baseline.value: No regions provide protection services to vulnerable girls and boys

target.value: 2015:3 regions provide protection services to vulnerable girls and boys

title.narrative: Develop a strategy for psychosocial support in emergencies

baseline.value: No strategy for Child Protection in Emergencies developed

actual.value: 2015:No specific strategy available. CP emergency partners identified and skills to address emergencies improved.
